Like this is a new thing Enchanters made out like bandits in SOL and POP. Manaburn ? pffft any chanter with kei to sell made more PP than whole manaburn squads and they did it day in day out with no controversy. One of the most sought after grouping classes it wasn't to hard for chanters to get direcharm as well in a relatively short time. Enchanters who wanted a little action were soloing in Kael and selling armor MQ's early after SOL's release. Forget porting making stat jewely was where the plat was all the way until cultural armor with good stats was put ingame. Even then most of the smiths I see or know are alts of enchanters. If mages had a designer/advocate like enchanters we would have gotten the tools to solo in NTOV pre pop P. I too want to solo with an LFG tag up on the extreme offhand chance something even more lucrative or interesting is offered P The day KEI was put in game with no level limit was the day EQ began its current downward slide imo.I am glad that there are people who have some jawdropping soloing skills and are having a blast with them. Hop in to the way back machine Sherman P when you chain pulled seafuries and your only concern was bringing enough malachite so you did not have to move. Or you soloed/duoed for some damn nice items for thier time. Batskull /cougarclaw earrings for 500 + each anyone and you got xp doing it to). Astral cloak or leggings anyone,footpads of the tiger? Rallic pack for 2500+ anyone.This is the same thing just not for mages atm is all. In the end if you had a good time and made some good friends you got your money's worth out of EQ. Hopefully the developers of the next mmporgs learn something from EQ's mistakes and its successes. I think that EQ positives far outweigh the negatives and though the game is tired and dated its still a good deal of fun ). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farslayer77>Farslayer77</A> at: 2/21/03 7:36:34 pm<br></i></td>